"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-caeleb-dressel-simone-manuel-comebacks-complete-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Shortly after noon Wednesday, August Dressel was out and about on the streets of Indianapolis.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 94, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 81, \"end\": 93, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis_500\", \"score\": 0.7315107019263765, \"rank\": 0.3646423763701274, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis_500\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis_500\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"August, just four months old, was being pushed in a stroller by his mom, Meghan, with aunt Sherridon Dressel walking alongside.\", \"from\": 95, \"to\": 222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 186, \"end\": 195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherridon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sherridon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherridon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherridon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sucking on a pacifier in the midwestern heat, August was blissfully unaware of what hovered over his father.\", \"from\": 223, \"to\": 331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Caeleb Dressel was swimming for a spot on the U.S. Olympic team after two years of fleeing the sport and meandering back.\", \"from\": 333, \"to\": 454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 333, \"end\": 347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caeleb Dressel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Becoming a father was part of the journey, perhaps the kind of life development that can take a man\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s mind away from being his own harshest critic.\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Simone Manuel had a major life change of her own in recent months\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094getting married.\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 690, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 606, \"end\": 619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Manuel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Manuel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Manuel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She, too, had wandered into physical and mental disarray in recent years, unsure if she would ever be a great swimmer again.\", \"from\": 691, \"to\": 815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On an electric and emotional night at Lucas Oil Stadium Wednesday, Dressel and Manuel came back.\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 913, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 896, \"end\": 902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"score\": 0.4808914122170371, \"rank\": 0.7224784320463414, \"text\": \"Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were tears, from Manuel on the podium and from Dressel as he held August and kissed him.\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 1008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 937, \"end\": 943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"score\": 0.4808914122170371, \"rank\": 0.7224784320463414, \"text\": \"Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were smiles at a mission at least partly accomplished by two 27-year-olds who bear the scars of their unkind sport.\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1130, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At another point in time, it would have been deeply disappointing for the American record-holders in the 100 freestyle to finish third (Dressel) and fourth (Manuel) in that event.\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1311, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1206, \"end\": 1214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.5665071174650459, \"rank\": 0.7652024073292456, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1289, \"end\": 1295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"score\": 0.4808914122170371, \"rank\": 0.7224784320463414, \"text\": \"Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But not at this point.\", \"from\": 1312, \"to\": 1334, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re both Olympians for the third time, navigating through a purgatory that remains partially mysterious.\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re still capable of elite performances, and still capable of bringing fans to their feet.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The largest crowd ever for anindoor swim meet, 22,209 strong, bathed them in welcoming cheers.\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThis sport, realistically speaking, has been a very lonely place for me,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Manuel said.\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1731, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1719, \"end\": 1725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"score\": 0.4808914122170371, \"rank\": 0.7224784320463414, \"text\": \"Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think after Tokyo (in 2021) I felt even more alone.\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1788, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1749, \"end\": 1754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9707571745135668, \"rank\": 0.030123726815347404, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 Being in this arena and being surrounded by these fans has honestly been so healing.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Manuel spoke articulately about her journey back from overtraining syndrome, which left her a shell of her former self at Olympic Trials three years ago.\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 2035, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1882, \"end\": 1888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"score\": 0.4808914122170371, \"rank\": 0.7224784320463414, \"text\": \"Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She gritted out a spot on the team in the 50 freestyle, then got out of the pool for five months to rest.\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She changed coaches, moving to train with Bob Bowman at Arizona State, then arduously and incrementally dug herself out of a deep hole.\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2184, \"end\": 2187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"score\": 0.7451314724837238, \"rank\": 0.342044968991925, \"text\": \"Bob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bob_Weinstein\"}, {\"begin\": 2188, \"end\": 2194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bowman_Gum\", \"score\": 0.9065483060064073, \"rank\": 0.10308517855462694, \"text\": \"Bowman\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bowman_Gum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bowman_Gum\"}, {\"begin\": 2198, \"end\": 2211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona_State_University\", \"score\": 0.7074564526972631, \"rank\": 0.4135145617935294, \"text\": \"Arizona State\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona_State_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona_State_University\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI definitely think that through the process there were times where I was likewhy am I doing this?I can think back to certain meets and results that I had at those competitions, and you travel home on Sunday, and I am like, I really do not want to go to practice Monday.\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like I am not ready to go back just because I wasn't seeing the progress I wanted.\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2634, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSo I think there was a lot of ebbs and flows in the journey, but I do not think in my mind there ever was an option to quit.\", \"from\": 2636, \"to\": 2763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not know, getting through trials in 2021 was a tough journey, so I felt like, in some way, I had some armor to be able to get through this one.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Dressel did not speak publicly at all, as has been his recurring stance for nearly a year.\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 3007, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s press conference for the top four finishers in the event\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Chris Guiliano, Jack Alexy, Dressel and Hunter Armstrong\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094was canceled late Wednesday, ostensibly because Alexy was delayed in drug testing.\", \"from\": 3008, \"to\": 3220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3095, \"end\": 3099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"score\": 0.9796498311144074, \"rank\": 0.020771942929889438, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\"}, {\"begin\": 3119, \"end\": 3125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Biden\", \"score\": 0.9986904561991272, \"rank\": 0.001301647211882281, \"text\": \"Hunter\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Biden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(He was outside the venue signing autographs not long after the interview was canceled, so that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s interesting.)\", \"from\": 3221, \"to\": 3334, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Dressel wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t going to show anyway.\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3377, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s become reclusive since his breakdown at the 2022 World Championships in Hungary, dropping out of the meet after two events and stopping swimming for months.\", \"from\": 3379, \"to\": 3542, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3458, \"end\": 3465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"score\": 0.9999999686924643, \"rank\": 3.099108739040494e-08, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He immersed himself in therapy to deal with whatever was tormenting him.\", \"from\": 3543, \"to\": 3615, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here in Indianapolis last summer, Dressel attempted to come back at the U.S. National Championships.\", \"from\": 3617, \"to\": 3717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3625, \"end\": 3637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis_500\", \"score\": 0.7315107019263765, \"rank\": 0.3646423763701274, \"text\": \"Indianapolis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis_500\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indianapolis_500\"}, {\"begin\": 3694, \"end\": 3716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics_National_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.110976730437745e-16, \"text\": \"National Championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics_National_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics_National_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His lack of training showed, and he didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t come close to making the team.\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3793, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it at least was a start back, as he gradually put the pieces back together.\", \"from\": 3794, \"to\": 3873, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dressel returned to competition this spring and kept trending the right way through meets in March, April and May.\", \"from\": 3875, \"to\": 3989, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time he got to Indy, he was a reasonable facsimile of his old self\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094not Peak Caeleb, but once again one of the fastest men in America.\", \"from\": 3990, \"to\": 4132, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 100 free final Wednesday night, Dressel as usual was first to the 15-meter mark, when swimmers have to break the surface.\", \"from\": 4134, \"to\": 4262, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He slipped back to fourth at the turn, but closed furiously in the final meters to nearly nab first-place Guiliano and second-place Alexy.\", \"from\": 4263, \"to\": 4401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dressel\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s time of 47.53 seconds put him only .15 behind Guiliano.\", \"from\": 4402, \"to\": 4469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It also was his fastest time since 2021, when he won five gold medals in Tokyo and ruled the sport.\", \"from\": 4470, \"to\": 4569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4543, \"end\": 4548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9707571745135668, \"rank\": 0.030123726815347404, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the top six finishers all breaking 48 seconds, the collective 100 freestyle performances bodes well for the U.S. in the 400 freestyle relay.\", \"from\": 4571, \"to\": 4716, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The American men are under siege from competitors around the globe, but they can plant their flag with that relay early in the Olympic schedule.\", \"from\": 4717, \"to\": 4861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4721, \"end\": 4729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.5665071174650459, \"rank\": 0.7652024073292456, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Television_in_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cOh my God, top six under 48!\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Dressel exclaimed on NBC while looking at the scoreboard to see the results of the race.\", \"from\": 4863, \"to\": 4986, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4919, \"end\": 4922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9984341450018221, \"rank\": 0.0015683107452872623, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThat\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s quick.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Then Dressel nearly left the pool deck without doing the one thing everyone who makes the Olympic team longs to do\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094signing the oversized Paris postcard.\", \"from\": 4987, \"to\": 5164, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5149, \"end\": 5154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.923857642791521e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Guiliano had to grab him and remind him to put his autograph on it.\", \"from\": 5165, \"to\": 5232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The women were similarly fast, with seven out of eight breaking 54 seconds and the top two\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Kate Douglass and Torri Huske\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094breaking 53.\", \"from\": 5234, \"to\": 5371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5327, \"end\": 5340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Manuel did not quite go as fast Wednesday as she had in the first two rounds, finishing in 53.25 seconds.\", \"from\": 5372, \"to\": 5477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5372, \"end\": 5378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"score\": 0.4808914122170371, \"rank\": 0.7224784320463414, \"text\": \"Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it was enough to lock up another Summer Games appearance for a woman with five Olympic medals on her r\\u00c3\\u00a9sum\\u00c3\\u00a9.\", \"from\": 5478, \"to\": 5592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHearing Simone's story, it's very moving,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Gretchen Walsh, who finished third.\", \"from\": 5594, \"to\": 5682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5647, \"end\": 5661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gretchen Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think she's a great example to just put into perspective what you can go through in this sport.\", \"from\": 5683, \"to\": 5783, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's very unforgiving.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cShe\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a true inspiration to everyone on Team USA.\", \"from\": 5784, \"to\": 5863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5854, \"end\": 5862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9990237375360783, \"rank\": 0.0007662525370105492, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m excited to have her as a role model out in Paris, and I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m just looking forward to experiencing my first Olympics with her third Olympics, and it should be one for the books for sure.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Dressel will have two other chances to make the team in individual events, in the 100 butterfly and 50 freestyle.\", \"from\": 5864, \"to\": 6172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5913, \"end\": 5918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.923857642791521e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Manuel also will have a chance in the 50.\", \"from\": 6173, \"to\": 6214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6173, \"end\": 6179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"score\": 0.4808914122170371, \"rank\": 0.7224784320463414, \"text\": \"Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manuel_I_Komnenos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They may not make it, and they may never be the swimmers they once were.\", \"from\": 6215, \"to\": 6287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But they came back to the sport at the Olympic level, after falling to the depths.\", \"from\": 6288, \"to\": 6370, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s victory in and of itself.\", \"from\": 6371, \"to\": 6405, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 6407, \"to\": 6433, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Pat Forde is a senior writer for Sports Illustrated who covers college football and college basketball as well as the Olympics and horse racing.\", \"from\": 6434, \"to\": 6642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6498, \"end\": 6507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_Forde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pat Forde\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_Forde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_Forde\"}, {\"begin\": 6531, \"end\": 6549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9301149593348068e-31, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He cohosts the College Football Enquirer podcast and is a football analyst on the Big Ten Network.\", \"from\": 6643, \"to\": 6741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6725, \"end\": 6740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Ten_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Big Ten Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Ten_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Ten_Network\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He previously worked for Yahoo Sports, ESPN and The (Louisville) Courier-Journal.\", \"from\": 6742, \"to\": 6823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6767, \"end\": 6779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_Sports\", \"score\": 0.815096196264302, \"rank\": 0.22684904844294426, \"text\": \"Yahoo Sports\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 6781, \"end\": 6785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1657956657095362e-20, \"text\": \"ESPN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Forde has won 28 Associated Press Sports Editors writing contest awards, has been published three times in the Best American Sports Writing book series, and was nominated for the 1990 Pulitzer Prize.\", \"from\": 6824, \"to\": 7023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6841, \"end\": 6857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999982510417, \"rank\": 1.7489244243640943e-09, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 6935, \"end\": 6963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Best_American_Sports_Writing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Best American Sports Writing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Best_American_Sports_Writing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resou